headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges scored 26 points and the Brooklyn Nets moved to the verge of a playoff spot by beating the Detroit Pistons 123-108 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets beat Pistons 123-108, close in on playoff berth

events.name: New York Knicks at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Immanuel Quickley scored 39 points, one shy of his career high, and Quentin Grimes had a career-high 36 in the New York Knicks' 138-129 victory over the Indiana Pacers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Quickley, Grimes lead Knicks past Pacers, 138-129

headlines.description: — Trae Young returned after missing one game with the flu and scored 25 points and had 16 assists to help the travel-weary Atlanta Hawks overwhelm shorthanded Washington 134-116 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young has 25 as Hawks gain momentum, beat Wizards 134-116

headlines.description: — Malcolm Brogdon scored 29 points and hit two late free throws to help the Boston Celtics hold on for a 97-93 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics wrap up East No. 2 seed with 97-93 win over Raptors

headlines.description: — Wrapping up the top seed in the NBA playoffs was the order of business for the Milwaukee Bucks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks wrap up top seed in NBA with 105-92 victory over Bulls

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — While Herbert Jones makes his living as the Pelicans’ top defender, he can also punish opponents who underestimate his shot.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pelicans top Grizzlies 138-131 in OT, earn play-in spot

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving had already sparked a rally to put the Dallas Mavericks in front when he hit a gravity-defying shot that helped seal a victory to keep their postseason hopes alive.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavs keep play-in hopes alive with 123-119 win over Kings

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — The battle of Los Angeles was no contest. The quest for the highest possible playoff seed is another story for the Clippers and Lakers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Powell and Leonard lead Clippers over Lakers, 125-118
